---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Bulgaria Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/bulgaria/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Romania for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/romania' },
  { title: 'Greece for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/greece' },
  { title: 'Turkey for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/turkey' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'bulgariaFit', header: 'Bulgaria Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BGN 550-780/mo', bulgariaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BGN 650-920/mo', bulgariaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BGN 500-720/mo', bulgariaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BGN 470-680/mo', bulgariaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Bulgarian NHIF', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'N/A', monthlyFrom: '8% income', bulgariaFit: 'For Residents' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'BGN 500-780', annual: 'BGN 6,000-9,360' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'BGN 700-1,050', annual: 'BGN 8,400-12,600' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'BGN 950-1,400', annual: 'BGN 11,400-16,800' },
  { category: 'Bulgarian Public (NHIF)', monthly: '8% of income', annual: 'Contribution-based' },
  { category: 'Bulgarian Private Clinic', monthly: 'BGN 50-200', annual: 'BGN 600-2,400' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Bulgaria 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Bulgaria. EU's most affordable living, Black Sea coast, Sofia hospitals, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Bulgaria"
  subheadline="Bulgaria offers the EU's lowest cost of living, Black Sea beaches, mountain retreats, and EU membership—an increasingly popular choice for budget-conscious retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/bulgaria-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Bulgaria</h2>
  <p>
    Bulgaria is the EU's most affordable country, offering stunning value for retirees. Black Sea beaches, ski resorts, hot springs, and rich history add appeal. EU membership means Schengen access (joining 2025), euro adoption path, and European standards improving steadily.
  </p>

  <p>
    Sofia provides capital-city amenities with surprisingly good healthcare. Plovdiv offers culture and charm as European Capital of Culture. Varna and Burgas deliver coastal living. Bansko attracts skiers and mountain lovers. Smaller towns offer extreme affordability.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Improving; private sector good in cities</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Bulgarian; Russian understood; English growing</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> BGN 1,500-3,000/month (~€750-1,500); EU's cheapest</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Continental; hot summers, cold winters (milder coast)</li>
      <li><strong>EU Status:</strong> Full EU member (not yet Eurozone; uses BGN)</li>
      <li><strong>Value:</strong> Exceptional for budget-conscious retirees</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Bulgaria's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Bulgaria has public healthcare through NHIF (National Health Insurance Fund) funded by social contributions. Quality varies—public hospitals can be dated with long waits. Private healthcare has grown significantly and offers modern facilities in major cities.
  </p>

  <p>
    Sofia's private hospitals (Tokuda, Acibadem, Medica) provide excellent care at fraction of Western prices. Private clinics in Plovdiv, Varna are good. Many Bulgarians and expats rely on private care for anything beyond basic needs. Medical tourism is growing.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Public vs Private Reality</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Bulgarian public healthcare is improving but remains below Western standards. Equipment can be old, facilities dated, English limited. Most expats rely on private healthcare—it's affordable (consultations from BGN 50-100) and provides much better experience. Budget for private care.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Bulgaria offers welcoming options for retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Type D Long-Stay Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For those demonstrating sufficient means (typically BGN 1,200+/month income) and health insurance. Valid up to 1 year, renewable. Leads to residence permit. Straightforward process.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    After D visa, apply for residence permit. Requires proof of accommodation, health insurance, financial means. Valid 1 year initially, renewable. After 5 years can apply for permanent residence.
  </p>

  <h3>EU/EEA Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Free movement applies. Register with local authorities after 3 months. Must demonstrate sufficient resources and health coverage. Full access to Bulgarian healthcare once contributing.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Bulgaria:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Visa application:</strong> Comprehensive health insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>EU citizens:</strong> EHIC initially; can join Bulgarian system</li>
    <li><strong>After residence:</strong> Can voluntarily join NHIF or maintain private</li>
    <li><strong>Private recommended:</strong> Most expats prefer private healthcare quality</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Bulgaria</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential for visa applications. Given public healthcare limitations, most seniors maintain international coverage for quality care and potential evacuation to better facilities. Bulgarian private care is cheap enough to pay cash for routine needs.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Bulgaria, these providers offer good coverage at Bulgarian cost levels:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Bulgaria</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good European network, evacuation included</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive Balkans pricing</li>
    <li><strong>Bulgarian Private:</strong> Tokuda, Acibadem for local care</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage and pricing from providers that accept seniors for Bulgaria.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Bulgaria are among the EU's lowest:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> BGN 5,000+ deductible significantly reduces premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Pay-as-you-go:</strong> Bulgarian private care is so cheap, cash payments work</li>
    <li><strong>Regional exclusions:</strong> Excluding expensive regions reduces costs</li>
    <li><strong>NHIF backup:</strong> Join Bulgarian public system as secondary coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Budget Retiree, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,500/month Social Security. Seeking maximum value in EU.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care for visa and comprehensive coverage. Use Tokuda/Acibadem private hospitals. Cigna excluded for US visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~BGN 600/month (~$325). Lives comfortably on remaining pension. Excellent value.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Couple, Both 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Post-Brexit, seeking affordable EU life. Combined pension £2,800/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global for both. Live in Plovdiv for culture and value. Private healthcare for quality.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~BGN 1,800/month combined (~£780). Live very well on remaining pension.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: German EU Citizen, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> EU citizen moving from Munich to Varna coast. German pension €1,600/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> EU rights apply. Register for Bulgarian coverage. Add Cigna for Germany visits. Use private clinics locally.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Bulgarian public + Cigna (Bulgaria excluded) ~€280/month. Lives excellently on coast.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Bulgaria really that cheap?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—the EU's most affordable country. A comfortable life costs BGN 2,000-3,000/month (€1,000-1,500). Restaurant meals from BGN 10-20. Rent from BGN 400-800 in cities. Private healthcare consultations BGN 50-100. It's 50-70% cheaper than Western Europe.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Bulgarian healthcare adequate for seniors?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Private healthcare in Sofia is quite good—modern hospitals, trained doctors, reasonable prices. Outside Sofia quality drops. For complex conditions, international insurance with evacuation coverage is important. Some seniors travel to Greece or Turkey for specialized care.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I use English in Bulgaria?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Limited outside Sofia's private hospitals and tourist areas. Bulgarian uses Cyrillic alphabet, which adds challenge. Russian is more widely understood (older generation). Younger Bulgarians increasingly speak English. Learning basic Bulgarian significantly helps daily life.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">When does Bulgaria join Schengen?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Bulgaria joined Schengen air borders in March 2024, with full land borders expected 2025. This means easier EU travel. Bulgaria is also on path to euro adoption (target 2025-2026), which will simplify finances for those with euro income.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for Bulgaria.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Bulgarian authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
